This work uses an historical approach to understanding the routines an everyday habit in household in relation 
to energy consumption, how the household appliances impact energy distributed to each household. 
This report also considers of how social, cultural and physical infrastructure that changes householdsâ€™ routine daily,
routine is very important in understanding the energy consumption behaviour of households. 
The perspective of this project is to understand the consumption pattern in households and to 
predict future energy consumption in relation to total energy delivered to a household and 
the electrical parts consuming the energy and it impact on demand-side energy management. 
This report uses quarterly consumption for 2007 with data gathered between January and June of the same year. 
The result shows four household parts consumption and intensity in relations to active power.
